 1.0, \"rank\": 2.914739618712637e-65, \"text\": \"Eric Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eric_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_China\", \"score\": 0.9017873724459956, \"rank\": 0.10885448401637698, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Flying Scotsman\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 340}, {\"ngram\": \"missionary parents\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 391}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 401}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m sprint\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 420}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1924 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was obviously well before my time, but the nostalgia stems from the lasting impact on me of thebrilliant 1981 film Chariots of Firethat recounted Liddell's story.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9888186440011846, \"rank\": 0.011307503810431678, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my time\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"the nostalgia\", \"from\": 493, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"the lasting impact\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 536}, {\"ngram\": \"thebrilliant 1981 film Chariots\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"Firethat\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The backstory of this man provides a curious challenge for a secular age that prizes success and competition and winning above all else.\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The backstory\", \"from\": 618, \"to\": 631}, {\"ngram\": \"this man\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 643}, {\"ngram\": \"a curious challenge\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"a secular age\", \"from\": 677, \"to\": 690}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 703, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 726}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Liddell was a student at Edinburgh University and the fastest sprinter in the UK and went to Paris as Britain's great hope for gold in the 100m.\", \"from\": 756, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9888186440011846, \"rank\": 0.011307503810431678, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}, {\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\", \"score\": 0.9999999998494786, \"rank\": 1.5057432915452126e-10, \"text\": \"Edinburgh University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Edinburgh\"}, {\"begin\": 834, \"end\": 836, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999989738467583, \"rank\": 1.0257125831423877e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 849, \"end\": 854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983774615, \"rank\": 1.6226279561299501e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a student\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest sprinter\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"Britain's great hope\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 887}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 900}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he discovered as the British Olympic team left for Paris that the 100m heats were to be held on a Sunday.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 1010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999895578352563, \"rank\": 1.0442273923445439e-05, \"text\": \"British Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999983774615, \"rank\": 1.6226279561299501e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 100m heats\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 981}, {\"ngram\": \"a Sunday\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a committed Christian he believed that one of the Ten Commandments about honouring the Sabbath meant no competitive sport on Sunday and he provoked a team crisis by refusing to run.\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9993304618009136, \"rank\": 0.0006699865785258278, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1101, \"end\": 1108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabbath_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9993018956411891, \"rank\": 0.0006984284513495128, \"text\": \"Sabbath\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabbath_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sabbath_in_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Ten Commandments\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"no competitive sport\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1135}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1145}, {\"ngram\": \"a team crisis\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How could he let himself and his country down over such a pedantic rule?\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1268, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his country\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"such a pedantic rule\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surely his first duty was to his nation.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1309, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his first duty\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"his nation\", \"from\": 1298, \"to\": 1308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up for Guardian Australia's free morning and afternoon email newsletters for your daily news roundup This sort of religion sounds ridiculous to most ears and incomprehensibly heavy on duty to God.\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1323, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guardian Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"afternoon email newsletters\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"your daily news\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1408}, {\"ngram\": \"This sort\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1426}, {\"ngram\": \"religion\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"most ears\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"duty\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1504}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I grew up in a family and church that believed there should be no Sunday sport and I still remember feeling great guilt when for the first time in the late 80s I sneaked off on a Sunday to watch my Essendon Bombers play at the MCG.\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Essendon_Football_Club\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Essendon Bombers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Essendon_Football_Club\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Essendon_Football_Club\"}, {\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Cricket_Ground\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.654467506871496e-14, \"text\": \"MCG\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Cricket_Ground\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne_Cricket_Ground\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a family\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"church\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1550}, {\"ngram\": \"no Sunday sport\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1596}, {\"ngram\": \"great guilt\", \"from\": 1626, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 1647, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"the late 80s\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"a Sunday\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1703}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I strongly identified with Eric's dilemma.\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1792, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Eric's dilemma\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Chariots of Fire came out, I was surprised and buoyed by its lionising of Liddell's sense of duty to God above all else.\", \"from\": 1794, \"to\": 1919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1873, \"end\": 1880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"score\": 0.9888186440011846, \"rank\": 0.011307503810431678, \"text\": \"Liddell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chuck_Liddell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chariots\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"Fire\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"its lionising\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"duty\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1896}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I saw the film when visiting Oxford in 1981 and remember the whole cinema erupting into booing.\", \"from\": 1920, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1949, \"end\": 1955, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.9999755135019156, \"rank\": 2.4487097422059475e-05, \"text\": \"Oxford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the film\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1934}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole cinema\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1993}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That was because Eric's competitor Harold Abrahams scorned his Scottish counterpart for not being from the finest university in the country (Cambridge).\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2051, \"end\": 2066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harold Abrahams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Abrahams\"}, {\"begin\": 2079, \"end\": 2087, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people\", \"score\": 0.9986883790093253, \"rank\": 0.0012979347016704667, \"text\": \"Scottish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 2157, \"end\": 2166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"score\": 0.9998195405844694, \"rank\": 0.00018049198207609364, \"text\": \"Cambridge\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Cambridge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Eric's competitor\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"the finest university\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2140}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 2144, \"to\": 2155}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Otherwise, the cinema crowd was reverently silent, moved and engrossed by Eric's sense of duty.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2264, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the cinema crowd\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2196}, {\"ngram\": \"Eric's sense\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2255}, {\"ngram\": \"duty\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The audience did not miss the irony of the Prince of Wales being brought in to convince Eric to put country before God and to stop being ridiculous and run.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2421, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The audience\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2277}, {\"ngram\": \"the irony\", \"from\": 2291, \"to\": 2300}, {\"ngram\": \"the Prince\", \"from\": 2304, \"to\": 2314}, {\"ngram\": \"Wales\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"Eric\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2357}, {\"ngram\": \"country\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2372}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 2380, \"to\": 2383}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was the same Prince of Wales who, as King Edward 8th, later abdicated and in the eyes of many of his subjects failed his duty to them and the nation.\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2464, \"end\": 2468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"score\": 0.8885466735617153, \"rank\": 0.12542687924818913, \"text\": \"King\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monarch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same Prince\", \"from\": 2431, \"to\": 2446}, {\"ngram\": \"Wales\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2455}, {\"ngram\": \"the eyes\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"his subjects\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2536}, {\"ngram\": \"his duty\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2552}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The plot had a remarkable twist.\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2610, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The plot\", \"from\": 2578, \"to\": 2586}, {\"ngram\": \"a remarkable twist\", \"from\": 2591, \"to\": 2609}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eric stayed true to his perceived duty and pulled out of the heats.\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Eric\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2615}, {\"ngram\": \"his perceived duty\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"the heats\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then at the last moment his Olympic team entered him in the 400m, not his event nor one for which he had trained.\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2796, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last moment\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2706}, {\"ngram\": \"his Olympic team\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2723}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400m\", \"from\": 2739, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"not his event\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He claimed gold in a world record time of 47.6 seconds.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2852, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2812}, {\"ngram\": \"a world record time\", \"from\": 2816, \"to\": 2835}, {\"ngram\": \"47.6 seconds\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2851}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had fulfilled the duty he felt to a higher calling, willing to sacrifice his specialist event with all his training, but remarkably managed to win anyway.\", \"from\": 2853, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the duty\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2878}, {\"ngram\": \"a higher calling\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2906}, {\"ngram\": \"his specialist event\", \"from\": 2929, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"all his training\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His fierce sprinting British competitor Abrahams ran and did win the 100m for Britain.\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3032, \"end\": 3039, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.5380380290312884, \"rank\": 0.573362842920299, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 100m\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3084}, {\"ngram\": \"Britain\", \"from\": 3089, \"to\": 3096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team were triumphant.\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3123, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The team\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a true story and a feelgood story that offers a vision of there being a higher duty than one's own personal success and national glory.\", \"from\": 3125, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a true story\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3142}, {\"ngram\": \"a feelgood story\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"a vision\", \"from\": 3176, \"to\": 3184}, {\"ngram\": \"a higher duty\", \"from\": 3200, \"to\": 3213}, {\"ngram\": \"one's own personal success\", \"from\": 3219, \"to\": 3245}, {\"ngram\": \"national glory\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a strange idea to valorize in a 1981 film and would be even stranger in today's age of self-promotion, nationalism and narcissism.\", \"f